## §A.6 Stage-1+ T3 closure path (post-RSC saturation)

RSC loop saturated 2026-05-08 (recipe §7.2 sat-1 + sat-2 ✓). All four
preregistered falsifiers (F-SPACE-1/2/3/4) reach 67 % closure (T1 ✓ + T2 ✓).
T3 (empirical hardware feed) is the only remaining tier — out of recipe
scope per §9 since it cannot be closed by adding `.hexa` scripts alone.

Path to 100 % closure follows the **hexa-antimatter Phase C/D/E** template:

| Phase | Layer | Artefact | hexa-space scope |
|:------|:------|:---------|:-----------------|
| **C** | sim-firmware | `firmware/sim/<name>.hexa` state-machine + DAC/ADC pipeline + safety interlock verification | 4 controllers — one per F-SPACE-N |
| **D** | HDL skeleton | `firmware/hdl/<name>.v` Verilog top-level (Vivado synthesis OK; not flashable) | 4 FPGA boards (Xilinx UltraScale+ family / STM32H7 MCU) |
| **E** | physical board | actual silicon (procured / fabricated) + bench validation | ✗ funding-blocked |

### §A.6.1 Stage-1 controller catalog (Phase C/D targets)

- **HEXA-ORBIT-01** (F-SPACE-1) — Mercury perihelion advance pipeline.
  STM32H7 + USNO MICA ephemeris reader + Kepler integrator. Validates
  43″/century anomaly via numerical comparison to GR + n=6 closed-form.
- **HEXA-LAUNCH-01** (F-SPACE-2) — Falcon 9 webcast telemetry capture.
  Xilinx Zynq UltraScale+ (XCZU7EV) + HDMI 1080p capture + on-screen
  T+/altitude/velocity OCR + Tsiolkovsky Δv reconstruction.
- **HEXA-DXA-01** (F-SPACE-3) — bone-density timeseries fitter.
  STM32H7 + USB DXA scanner data parser + τ=4 phase exp-decay fit
  (Sibonga 2007 t½ = 6 mo) + NASA Twin Study comparator.
- **HEXA-RAPTOR-01** (F-SPACE-4) — Starship cluster telemetry ingester.
  Xilinx Kintex UltraScale (XCKU040) + same OCR pipeline as LAUNCH-01
  re-targeted to Starship webcast overlay (33-Raptor stage-1 burn) +
  σ·n/φ−3 = 33 cluster-scaling validation.

Phase C+D land in `firmware/sim/` and `firmware/hdl/` respectively;
Phase E remains gated on funding (estimated ≈ $25k / board procurement).

### §A.6.2 Phase E procurement-prep (added 2026-05-08)

Each Stage-1 controller ships per-board procurement docs in
`firmware/board/<slug>/`:

- `SCHEMATIC.md` — block diagram + key net list + power tree + decoupling
- `BOM.csv` — line-item bill-of-materials with Digi-Key part numbers,
  qty, unit price, extended price, prototype + qty-5 totals
- `PCB.md` — stack-up + board outline + routing rules + impedance + EMC
- `COMMISSIONING.md` — bench bring-up checklist with PASS/FAIL gates
  and the **F-SPACE-N closure event** that flips T3 from ✗ to ✓
- `<slug>.kicad_sch` — KiCad 7+ S-expression root-sheet skeleton
  (opens cleanly; populate from SCHEMATIC.md §2)

Stage-1 program total ≈ **$26 k** (5× boards each + tools, within §A.6
~$25 k envelope; Vivado license shared across LAUNCH-01 + RAPTOR-01).

Phase E completes the **closure path** documentation; Phase F (physical
board procurement) remains funding-blocked. Once any single board
arrives + Phase G commissioning passes its closure-event gate, the
corresponding F-SPACE-N flips to 100 % closure (T1 ✓ + T2 ✓ + T3 ✓).
